@FastAndFurious005 It's actually a thumb.

It's supposed to be a joke. See, when artists paint, they usually stick their thumb out (as Sonic is doing) in a way to... I don't know, focus their paintbrushes or something. But as you can see, Sonic was not just doing that, he was using his thumb as a model, resulting in a punchline of a painting of what is indeed a thumb.

I hope no one starts saying it's a toe again after I post this...
